This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with adversarial examples and their impact on deep neural networks in image classification tasks. The paper also proposes a generative network to craft adversarial patterns, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with different types of images, including paintings and cartoons, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
